  "prompt": "What is the best way to restore my lost Yahoo toolbar?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to restore a lost Yahoo toolbar:\n\n1. For Web Browsers:\n\u2022 Open your browser\n\u2022 Go to Yahoo's official toolbar download page\n\u2022 Download and reinstall the toolbar\n\u2022 Follow installation instructions\n\u2022 Restart your browser\n\n2. For Internet Explorer:\n\u2022 Click \"Tools\" menu\n\u2022 Select \"Toolbars\"\n\u2022 Check/enable Yahoo toolbar\n\u2022 If missing, download from Yahoo's website\n\n3. For Chrome/Firefox:\n\u2022 Visit Chrome Web Store or Firefox Add-ons\n\u2022 Search for \"Yahoo toolbar\"\n\u2022 Click \"Add to Chrome/Firefox\"\n\u2022 Follow installation prompts\n\n4. Alternative Options:\n\u2022 Use Yahoo's homepage as start page\n\u2022 Add Yahoo search widget to browser\n\u2022 Use Yahoo search engine directly\n\n5. Troubleshooting:\n\u2022 Check browser extension settings\n\u2022 Ensure browser is updated\n\u2022 Disable conflicting extensions\n\u2022 Temporarily disable antivirus/firewall\n\nNote: Yahoo toolbars are less common now, and many modern browsers have integrated search and customization features that might replace traditional toolbars.\n\nIf problems persist, contact Yahoo support for specific guidance.",
